Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_520
Response Text: There can be some improvements made to the panel review process. It seems that a longer training may be needed for panelists and I like that the staff had planned to take the public review parts offline. However it would be nice to incorporate the ability to respond to 1-2 questions from the panelists or reduce the amount of applications they have to review in such a short time. I did do the Elevate panel reviewer position for the pilot year and it was definitely a tough and time consuming job. 

For Thrive, as an Asian American arts nonprofit leader, I really value the changes that were made and the Thrive applications and processes feel much more like they were supportive of the community work I'm doing for the AAPI community which has been historically and continues to be underfunded by wide margins in Austin. I think the Rubric is fantastic and when I was a reviewer for Elevate, the rubric and the training materials I often utilized helped me to stay on track and keep consistent when scoring.

